reviews_data.review_text: Central Milk Tea w/ boba and a #2 pork sandwich 😋 Excellent!!! Wish I lived closer to visit more often. Next time, I will try one of their lovely specialty teas.
Fantastic boba and food. The workers and owner are very friendly.

Today I went to grab me a drink with me and wife and today , what I saw was really disappointment and disagree , I saw this one man in back of the kitchen was really rude to her and he really was yelling at her wrong tone of the voice and she was very upset, he was really wrong doing that to her , yelling and slam thing , I hope she okay, he should be paition with her , she deserves better
Extensive drink selection with great prices. The interior is very cute, and the service was kind. Will be back often!

Delightful and authentic Vietnamese tea house/cafe. Clean, attractive and the staff was both warm, friendly and most helpful. Drinks and food were delicious and reasonably priced. Definitely one of my new “go to” spots!
BEST milk tea in plaza. they have non dairy options which a lot of other places don’t and the boba is soft and chewy not hard. this will be my new go to!
Yo that boba was good
Great customer service and boba is so good!! I recommend getting the honeydew smoothie ♥️

Hands down one of my favorite places in CLT. the banh mi is amazing, fresh, the bread is toasty, and great flavors. Every tea I have tried has been out of this world. Always an amazing experience with minimal wait times and a cozy and clean establishment.
Great service and very helpful!
Veggie Banh Mi was pretty delicious.
Not good, just ice, lacks flavor.. too expensive for just ice
Came in for bubble tea, which were delicious. It smelled amazing in there so I’ll have to come back to try the food.
It's okay. Beverages were good, awkward atmosphere though. Might just be an off day judging from the other ratings.
This place is a hidden gem. I really miss Taiwan, and even though this is Vietnamese, they have mastered the art of bubble tea. We'll definitely come back!
Garbage!

Popped in today with my family after church.   What an amazing surprise.   Charlotte has great spots yet because it’s such a transplant city, you can easily get caught up in big box and corporate eateries.  This place is a neighborhood gem that feels extremely genuine and is indeed quickly becoming one of my favorite spots.   Had teas, tea cakes, smoothies, etc.   next week, I’ll be moving on to the beautiful looking bahn mi sandwiches and some finger foods.   If it’s as good as it looks, I’ll be back for another review.

Gotta love the soul and integrity of family owned businesses.
Summer Breeze tea with mango popping and grilled pork banh mi were very tasty. I’ll be back for sure.
The foods in there are refreshing.
Best bahn mi sandwiches & smoothies around! Reasonable prices & super friendly staff. 10/10!
I recommend the strawberry kiss
Delicious food, large variety of teas, sandwiches, and finger foods like fried tofu are also great. Prices are fair and reasonable.

I come here once a week while we're running errands and I always look forward to getting tea from them! The space is always clean and has a cozy atmosphere, and the staff are friendly. Whether it's a milk tea, a fruit tea, or a coffee, their drinks are all fantastic and there are no bad choices really. They also have some great sandwiches and desserts that I highly recommend.

really yummy low-key boba shop! I love that they added sugarcane drinks that are made in house. The Thai tea is my favorite because its brewed tea, not powder! Their milk teas are always my go to because it's not made with powder unlike some other places. As far as food goes, the banh mi is always fresh and delicious (would recommend the house special, grilled pork, or bulgogi). However, the meat patties (they have chicken or pork) are my absolute favorite! They are so crispy with flavorful meat on the inside. Highly recommend and support small family owned businesses!

First time here! We got a Wildberry tea with bubbles & Honey Milk tea with bubbles. Super good & original taste! Plus they sell Vietnamese foods & deserts which we have to come back & try. We do apologize for coming in 5 minutes before closing, but the employees were super nice. Thank you <3

Hidden gem! The on site manager is really friendly and you can tell he really cares about the quality of beverages and food served. This site has a wide variety of drinks and makes for a perfect quick stop to get refreshments. We tried the Vietnamese coffee and matcha cheesecake— both were delicious.

They also serve Vietnamese sandwiches.
Best boba tea in Charlotte- I always get the taro milk tea 1/2 sweet so good! Always smells so clean inside too. I’m told the food is awesome too but I’ve never tried it. Support small businesses!
Amazing Banh Mis and atmosphere. Great service and staff.
Very good and delicious. Definitely would come back ☺.

I have visited this place with some time to kill and I had the mango mason jar. I love the fruit in the mason jar and also the decorated fruit. This is a great drink. Definitely get it and also the guy at the front on the register was very nice to me that we go to the spot if you like Boba or tea it was very pretty inside as well which I really enjoyed. I love when a store feels very comforting and pretty.

The vanilla bean latte is my favorite thing in the world. I used to stop by occasionally for a milk tea when I was in the area (and I do vaguely remember they were good), but one day I got the vanilla bean latte on a whim and now my life is changed and that's the only thing I ever get here. I've probably gotten it about 10 times at this point and its always delicious & perfect every time. Obsessed.

Oh, and the staff is always great and the shop is cute, too. :)
This place has amazing food, atmosphere and service. The owner is very friendly, cool guy. Go here now!! I got the #10 (bulgogi)+egg rolls & left with a vanilla bean latte.🥰
Fantastic coffee, bubble tea and bahn mi! Fresh ingredients and wonderful service make this a great place.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Lemongrass Tofu Banh MI, Popcorn Chicken, Lemongrass Chicken

reviews_data.review_text: I always have great service and the food and boba are the best!
Best tea/ drinks in Charlotte, hands down. I try something new on the menu every time I come in and am never disappointed!
Delicious Lemongrass Tofu (dry) Bahnmi sandwich.
Un ambiente agradable
I love the attention and care that was given by the staff. I'll definitely be back.
I love this tea house! The staff was so friendly. My order was delicious. I wish I had more to say, but it was just 10/10 and I was in and out in 10 minutes. 🥰
I love this place! Staff is very friendly. The drinks are good and the cream brûlée is the bomb!!!!
Got the lemongrass chicken bahn mi and it was soooooo yummy.
Gongcha is legit and Share tea is nice but this is my spot! Clean, chill, quick, plus yummy food! Parking can be tight but I've always found a spot.
Loved the milk boba 💕 tea

My friends introduced me to this place, and I will say, It was an amazing experience!
The place was very lovely on the inside and I had no idea this place existed!
I would highly recommend the mango drink and a bulgogi sammich! The flavors are very strong with a touch of spice from the kimchi!
Staff were very nice, the passion fruit green tea boba and popcorn chicken is delicious!
All of their menu is good, staff is awesome. Highly recommend for singles, couples and families. Thank you for being a hidden gem.
Friendly service, great banh mi and great Viet Coffee as well
cute shop and has the best lychee black tea ever and no wait time, they never disappoint, every time im in the area i have to come

By far the best boba in NC, perfectly cooked pearls and wonderfully flavored tea, at a price less than half that of its competitors! Great fresh food, wonderful customer service, and a cute pleasant atmosphere. I don’t write reviews for places I like much, but I would feel guilty if I didn’t leave a good review.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Tofu Banh MI with Green Tea Bubble Tea

reviews_data.review_text: okay this is the best popcorn chicken ever and brown sugar boba is incredible also kinda cheap
A great spot to grab a yummy banh mi and a Thai tea!
I thought lula has the best Vietnamese coffee, til I tried this sea salt viet ice coffee!  I always love central tea house ice coffee but with this sea salt foam. Genius! Love it!

Great hole in the whole that many people don't know about they have amazing taro,mango, and pina-cola teas. I'm working my way down the list and haven't even gotten to their smoothies yet.and its all dairy free.

Wow! Just Wow! The Organic Matcha Latte with Coffee jellies is an absolute must try. My son ordered a coffee latte with coffee jellies. Love this place. We also ordered the grilled pork and the lemongrass chicken Banh Mi. Fantastic food and yummy drinks.
Really good coffee milk teas. Great food at affordable prices. Really nice owner.

I absolutely LOVE Central Tea House and I go here a lot! This was the first place where I ever tried banh mi, and it’s still the best I’ve had. Their lemongrass tofu banh mi is amazing. The veggies are always fresh and so flavorful.

Their boba tea is equally tasty, and some of my faves are: wintermelon, Thai, Central (their signature), and brown sugar milk tea.

Phu, the owner, is super nice, and I love supporting a locally-owned business!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Lemongrass Tofu, Fruit Danish, Lemon Black Tea

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Evangelia for your review, patron and support!

reviews_data.review_text: Really nice, well done place. Very clean and attentive. Great teas and coffee.

Good clean service. They make a decent vietnamese sandwich which is what makes me come back.  In comparison to other places this has to be the more delicious and better valued sandwich of the CLT area. Their boba is top notch & the plaza has some of the better stores of the city! Staff is nice and the cafe is clean. Don’t expect anything special with their food because it’s clearly not a full blown restaurant. I am a regular boba tea connoisseur and recommend this spot!
Delicious Boba, great customer service, clean shop. What's not to like?!
Coffee milk tea was great! Bahn mi was good too

Definitely don’t go here if you’re in a rush. However everything is delicious. The teas were awesome and the people are so sweet. Get the pork pastry!! So good and so yum. Just takes a little while but it’s made to order. 9/10. Would definitely go again.

Couldn’t order a veggie only banh mi sandwich.. Literally just don’t add any meat or tofu.

I offered to pay for a tofu sandwich and asked them to not add the tofu. The woman at the register said they can’t do that.

So you mean to tell me you HAVE to add meat to a sub even though the customer doesn’t want it? You can’t just leave the veggies on as is?

The chef is literally behind you just ask them to not add meat to it.

Very annoying considering we spent $20+ on drinks.

There is a very nice and calm coffee shop type of atmosphere. I ordered a Vietnamese coffee and added coffee flavored jellies which was delicious. We enjoyed the pastries and the food, too. Menu pricing was very affordable compared to the inflated prices I am used to seeing now a days. To top it all off the staff was so kind. We will be coming back often.

No matter how good the drinks/food are... its always the same 2 moody girls that just seem like they are deeply unhappy with their job and it reflects with how they interact with their customers. The older and younger guy are nice at least.
Very cute little tea shop with friendly service and delicious bubble tea. An hour away from my home and I'll be coming again.

Soooo I went yesterday for the first time. Taste wise it was solid 9/10! The boba wasn't watered down at all. The popping boba was real and natural tasting unlike most shops. But… I don’t know how I felt about the service. I ordered the butterfly pea tea with lychee popping boba + regular boba. I received it and it looked great, although, I got the wrong toppings. I let them know they were the wrong toppings, apologizing. Maybe they were just tired but they seemed very annoyed. Once they returned… my butterfly pea tea was brown? Please someone tell me why is brown.. I thought it was the base they used but it should just be butterfly pea flowers in water, not another tea. I will change my review higher once I am aware that I actually got what I ordered. Because this was my first time ordering it, I know its supposed to be blue/purple but I don’t know how it tastes so I cant tell wether they got it wrong again or not, I was too afraid to ask.
So good 😍

Excellent tea, service, atmosphere, and music!

Update: still the best place eand price in the city! My favorite is their Taro smoothie with Boba.

Such a cute little tea
shop! My son and his friend wanted to try it so we drove the 40 min for the experience (we had dinner next door) and it was WORTH it. The teas we tried were delicious. I enjoyed my Honeydew slush so much I forgot to get pictures of the kids’ teas 😅

The restroom had a lock code, which is genius to make sure it stays clean and is still accessible to patrons. It’s important to have clean bathrooms ok? Even the bathroom was cute—and super clean. Which matters and gives confidence to me in a food establishment.

Can’t wait to go back and try more combos of teas, and that Matcha Cheesecake.
Very prompt
They have so many drink choices!

First time at Tea House. Very nice place and clean inside. Very nice ppl and very respect to customers, love the bubble tea. You guys should go check it out. The smoothie are very tasty, it good for hot day. Go check it out. 👍
Best boba tea in town!

My friend took me here on one of the hottest days in Charlotte so far. They had so many different types of teas, smoothies etc. I had the Taro Boba and it was outrageous. I love that you could order less sugar too. Can’t wait to go back.
Delicious teas and kind staff!!
Quick and easy service. Drinks are light and delicious 😋
Amazing Bahn mi, definitely recommend

I  come here every time I go to pick up my pets food. The staff is helpful and friendly and they have SEVERAL teas to choose from.  I have only had one that I didn't like. You can honestly get lost in the menu. Just try a new one each time you go but I will say the Peach Black Tea is my favorite! The food is amazing as well!
Hidden gem in Charlotte. You have to try this place. Milk tea, smoothies, great finger foods, and Banh Mi's

This is one of the few places in Charlotte to get flavored shave ice, also known as "snow"! $5.25 for your choice of flavor (we got taro), plus 3 toppings. It's the perfect, light dessert!

In addition to the usual boba milk tea choices, they also have banh mi sandwiches and other Taiwanese snacks we're looking forward to trying another time!

The "Sea Salt" series drinks must be an acquired taste. We tried a wintermelon sea salt milk tea, and it was definitely more salty than sweet. Not really to our liking, but glad we tried.
First impression, the blended boba tea was awesome! Taro is always my go-to flavor. Will definitely come back and try their Banh Mi next time too.
The best boba I have had thus far. im regretful I waited this long to come here.  I have tried a lot of tea houses by now and nothing can compare to them.
If you are addicted to sweets like my wife... This is the place to get your fix.
Great atmosphere and amazing tea, I recently moved to Charlotte and started working in the same shopping center and this will be my come to when I’m at work or just want a snack and drink one day

Great experience everyone here is wonderful. Great teas should check them out. Better than where I usually get chi tea. Also my son who’s three and is very picky loves there shaved strawberry with passion jelly and strawberry popping. If you know read this is the best place ever !!!!!
Got the Thai tea boba and lemongrass tofu banh mi, they were both very good! Maybe the best boba I've ever had, the pearls were so soft and just a great texture!
Great sandwiches and milk tea selection! Clean and cozy inside too, makes for a nice date.
They had great drinks and food!
love this small business! friendly, excellent service, and the best boba in town in my opinion.
Excellent boba
I usually never posts reviews, but this place deserves it. The milk teas with boba are absolutely delicious. I’ve tried a myriad of boba spots in Charlotte, and this one is by far the best.
The only boba place I like.
Accommodating and the tea is good. Consider halving the sugar though.

I’ve been here a couple times but I haven’t gotten the chance too review it but today I have some time. First I’d like too say the place is quite small but the atmosphere just screams peaceful, there are also plants on every table so it makes it nicer. They maintain the COVID guidelines which is 6 feet apart.
I had their strawberry smoothie boba and it was very refreshing, they have music playing in the background so it lightens the mood for anyone who might be in a terrible mood.
I’ve also just found out they have board games that you can play while drinking boba so that’s something else. They have sandwiches on their menu as well but those I haven’t tried yet so I can’t review those yet but other then that I recommend this place highly too anyone who wants too bring their date here.
I loved them so much the boba WAS AWESOME my mother loved the food as well my friend also enjoyed the boba her ABSOLUTELY RECOMMEND if you like bakery’s and boba😎✌🏽💖
First time trying. Very good experience.  Like oreo milk tea
Awesome banh mi. Vanilla milk tea is amazing
small place—would highly recommend for its excellent service and quality food/drinks. definitely making this a regular hangout!
Great mangonada and delicious Banh mi!
Lowkey spot with good boba and fast service. Diverse food options as well. Would recommend!
delicious tea, especially the winter melon fruit tea. it’s very low-key but definitely don’t overlook it. one of my favourite bubble tea places in charlotte

They have a very diverse choice of teas. They give you the choice of cold or hot for almost all options. Their egg tart was delicious as well. It's a nice spot to hang out inside or outside. There are two tables inside and two outside. If you're looking to try a new tea spot, this one is worth looking at.

The owner is very friendly and their bulgolgi banh mi is an absolute favorite of mine! This is also the only place where I was able to find egg tarts (or natas) and I can’t stop coming back for them. :) Love this place

Absolutely amazing here....the mega mango with rainbow 🌈 jelly's is brilliant it has little pieces of apples 🍎 and other fruits in it as well. And menu item #2 which is a sandwich is Devine. And the cute tea cake 🎂 is 🔥
1. Its a cozy little spot.
2.staff super friendly
3. Price's are like $9 and lower!!
4.support small business
Will return ...have return ....will continue to return!!
I just moved to the area 2 weeks ago and really like this place. I’ve already visited 3 times for tea
Best tea in town!

Stopped in for lunch after a hike and had the best experience! The Thai boba tea was fantastic, with perfect soft squishy boba. The real shing star was the bulgogi bahn mi. It's ruined me for all other sandwiches. Do your self a favor and get the egg add on. I just left and already can't wait to go back!
This place is the best! I always recommend Central Tea House for their delicious food, amazing drinks and wonderful people working there.
Deserves more love!!
the people there are sooo nice great boba I really recommend coming here!😁
Poor customer service! Even when owner be cashier ! When I try to order , He was rushing me at that time!

I stumbled on this cafe by chance and I’m glad I did. Their prices are quite affordable and they have a wide range of drink selections as well as snacks and pastries. Such as a variety of tea and bánh mì. Their boba is soft and chewy which is really good. My favorite is their oolong milk tea with 50% sugar.
I really like the vibe here. Good tea and sandwiches.
The best customer service, and the drinks are so good!!
The taro smoothie is great, all the pastries are awesome, and the BULGOGI sandwich is A1! The guy at the counter was super friendly, helpful, and incredibly polite. Will absolutely be coming back.
Had the tres leaches & passion tea~ very nice service & great tea plus the tres leaches was aromatic & delicate!
Great drink selection. Fun and family friendly. Delicious tea and Báhn Mi. Owner is very friendly. It’s very close to my job so I’ve found a new spot for after work!!!
This place is AMAZING and it is only my first time there mango green tea with boba and lychee jelly is to die for. And there is also a variety of drinks to choose from.I hope I come here more often
The food is delicious. The wide variety of teas are amazing. They have more than 20 different teas.

I used to go almost EVERY DAY when I worked close to here! The staff and owners are so wholesome, welcoming, and friendly here. The service is quick and the food is not only exceptionally priced but super delicious! My go to is the number 7 with a added egg and a raspberry lemon black tea with lychee popping pearls. It is a small shop which I love cause it's so cute! They also have really yummy deserts that they make there and little board games too! This place deserves more recognition for sure! 10/10 would recommend!!!
Everything here is worth double the price, especially the bahn mi. Phu's service is way superior and genuine as well.
Food and boba is on point!
Huge menu. Friendly service. Adorable set up.
Very friendly staff, good to have a small chat with. Tea was on top level. We've been to every bubble tea place in Charlotte, I definitely recommend this place. A+👌

I ordered a oolong milk tea, and it turned out extremely milky, and with no tea flavor at all.  Explained to the manager and tried to be nice about it and ended up being treat badly in return.  Not very good customer service.
The one on the right is the milky one, and I did not drink it.  Please be the judge.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello.  I apologize regarding the Oolong Milk Tea. I was trying to explain our policy of no refund or returns.
The picture on the right is the Oolong Milk Tea and the left is a Black Milk Tea. They are two different types of Milk Tea which produce different tastes and colors. You asked for exchange of the Oolong Milk Tea for a Black Milk Tea which we don’t mind exchange but not our policy. Sorry again for the situation and confusion.

reviews_data.review_text: Very nice cozy clean dining area. Quality drinks and food. Must see!
I love this place! Amazing prices on sandwiches and so yummy. I like the lemongrass tofu and sea salt viet coffee. The coffee could be addicting it’s so good.
This might be our new favorite boba place in town! The tea is fresh and there is a huge variety of drinks to try.

Service is quick. Tons of options for snacking. They even have games for you to play with friends. Definitely a great place for a quick hangout. The taro smoothie is pretty good. 👌 the shaved ice from San Fran has made my expectations too high so i didnt really care for the shaved ice here. Definitely will return to try out now things on the menu.
Delicious milk tea! Love the mochi topping!
Best boba tea I’ve had in Charlotte so far!
Best bubble tea on this side of town!
Loved all
The boba tea is amazing! There are so many drinks to choose from!

I would highly recommend you give it a try. Really good experience with owner, food, Boba tea, price, and setting. I will definitely be returning. I hope they out grow their present location, which is a small storefront shop.

We wanted a quick bite before a game, and decided on Vietnamese. We were going to stop at a Pho place, then we saw this next door. So glad we did! We ordered taro boba teas, a traditional banh mi pork sandwich, lemongrass chicken sandwich, and a traditional pork and egg steamed bun. Everything was delicious! My only remark is to ask for the bang mi buns to be less toasted (my preference).

The owner is super sweet and staff seem to enjoy their jobs, which makes for a great experience. They also offer pastries like: Napoleans, Tres Leches, Macaroons, cake slices, and cookies. Their milk tea, smoothie, and drink selection is vast, which I look to explore later.
Best Boba I ever taste in Charlotte, I’ve been everywhere.

This place was AMAZING. My wife and I are pretty picky with our bubble tea. We normally drive like an hour for some good bubble tea until we found this place. The flavor is delicious and creamy. They have a lot of options as well. We were definitely satisfied with our experience.
Good variety of offerings both in bahn mi and tea
love that they have bahn mis!

Amazing place for Bubble Tea, food, and dessert. The staff is always friendly and willing to assist any customer with their order. It is a great place to relax and grab a bite and play games with friends. My girlfriend and I love going here!
The pudding is very good, not too sweet or too eggy. Haven’t tried all the tea yet but the Fruity ones we got were good.

Cute little place with just a few small tables. It is a tea house, not a sit down restaurant. There must be 50 different types of tea! We tried three different ones and really enjoyed them. Be warned however, they can be VERY sweet. They have different levels of sweetness. Be sure to pick the one that matches your taste buds.

Food was great too. It was the best part. We had several sandwiches that were unusual and delicious. Great, distinct flavors. Unusually good bread.
Staff is wonderful!!!! They're like my asian family outside of my family!!!! Great selection of teas!!!!
Very delicious drinks!

This has to be one of the BEST places in Charlotte get banh mi and bubble tea!  The owner is Vietnamese, extremely sweet and friendly. This place offers a hospitable atmosphere to hang out with friends and/or get good food on the go. I will definitely return for more food!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your business and review.

reviews_data.review_text: U need to get there day dreamer special fruit tea its sooo good won't regret it and there sandwiches are the bomb as well really nice staff as well
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your business and the positive review.

reviews_data.review_text:
I love everything. I love the Bahn mi. My favorite is the bulgogi- it's a Korean BBQ, it's so good and the teas and smoothies are real fruit and milk!

I eat there multiple times a week. No regrets!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your business and the review.

reviews_data.review_text: I love the boboa tea here! Thai tea is my favorite
Very nice Banh mi and boboa tea shop, everyone was pleasant. The boboa tea is really good! There’s a wide variety and I can’t wait to try more!
Great food at very reasonable prices! A+
Disappointed. Over priced, long wait.. and no the place wasn’t even busy. Not sure why there are so many positive reviews on here. Maybe I’ll visit again and try out the food.... maybe.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Jessie. Thanks for your comment. We apologize for your negative experience. We were inexperienced than and since have learned from our mistakes. Hope you give us a second chance to gain your business and your appetite.

reviews_data.review_text: Pretty good tea joint, one of the only on the Central Blvd area. Small lounge area, but nicely decorated. Only thing I can say that I dislike is that toppings are at an added cost, whereas generally places like these toppings are generally free for one or 2, and then anymore is an extra cost.
My new favorite boba spot in Clt!! Such a convenient location, great drink selection, & everything is so fresh and greatly flavored!! Highly recommend!
Stopped in for tea today and loved it! Adorable tea/sandwich shop with a friendly staff. Great place to grab a quick bite to eat.

The place is nice.  Bright and welcoming!
Counter service with a smile (or 2).  It's in a good location as it's in the same plaza as the best Pho in Charlotte. I would save some room for an after pho smoothie or tea.  They have a lot of options so they will have what you want.  I had the original banh mi and it ranks up there with one of the best in Charlotte.  Definately stop by!
Amazing customer service! The drinks are delicious as well. They have lots of teas! You can even ask them to put it in a mason jar for you.

The shoppe is clean, the atmosphere is cozy, relaxing and the staffs are friendly. We wish we can come here everyday, bánh mì is delicious and a great way to go with bubble drink, so far we try four different bánh mì and all good. Definitely recommend.
Thank you so much and best wishes.

We had the Beach Bum tea, an Oreo shake and shared a Chicken sandwich. Everything was really good. So good that I ordered the beef sandwich and another Beach Bum tea to go. I’ll be back for sure to try different flavors!

Recommending this place for great boba tea (Sea Salt Matcha Latte is my favorite) and banh mi (Grilled Pork or Red Pork are my personal favorites) The staffs was helpful in recommending and explaining the menu. Will definitely be back.
This place is great! The variety seems endless and everything is really good. Really love their BahMi’s, especially their #7 grilled red pork and #10 bulgogi
That banh mis are delicious! They have a large variety of drinks which is impressive. My favorite drinks are the milk teas and sea salt drinks! Its a great place to visit with friends and family.

Place is amazing! The employees were so nice and very fast! I got the Central milk tea and it was super good! I can't wait to try more drinks because they have such a variety to choose from. They also have some fried foods along with Banh mi. Overall was a good experience, definitely recommend.

I was really excited for this place to open but was pretty disappointed. First of all, this is a tea house and it smells like funky seafood. It doesn’t give it a pleasant atmosphere or really give you much of an appetite for food or tea. Then I ordered a coconut milk tea, which was just okay. The tea tasted pretty great but the tapioca pearls were over cooked and mushy. For a simple order, and for a new restaurant, that doesn’t bode well. Overall, it’s not bad but I’d rather order a drink/food from Pho Hoa right next door (which I love). However, the menu is pretty expansive and offers unique drinks not easily available in Charlotte and I could have just caught a bad day. I’d give it another shot for sure. I hope things improve!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Hannah
Our apology for your negative experience. Since than, we have learned from our mistakes and made changes for a better customer experiences. Hope you will give us a second chance to gain your business. Thanks for your comment.

reviews_data.review_text: Great place for Vietnamese sandwich and milk tea. I love it!

reviews_data.review_text: Central Milk Tea w/ boba and a #2 pork sandwich 😋 Excellent!!! Wish I lived closer to visit more often. Next time, I will try one of their lovely specialty teas.
Fantastic boba and food. The workers and owner are very friendly.

Today I went to grab me a drink with me and wife and today , what I saw was really disappointment and disagree , I saw this one man in back of the kitchen was really rude to her and he really was yelling at her wrong tone of the voice and she was very upset, he was really wrong doing that to her , yelling and slam thing , I hope she okay, he should be paition with her , she deserves better
Extensive drink selection with great prices. The interior is very cute, and the service was kind. Will be back often!

Delightful and authentic Vietnamese tea house/cafe. Clean, attractive and the staff was both warm, friendly and most helpful. Drinks and food were delicious and reasonably priced. Definitely one of my new “go to” spots!
BEST milk tea in plaza. they have non dairy options which a lot of other places don’t and the boba is soft and chewy not hard. this will be my new go to!
Yo that boba was good
Great customer service and boba is so good!! I recommend getting the honeydew smoothie ♥️

Hands down one of my favorite places in CLT. the banh mi is amazing, fresh, the bread is toasty, and great flavors. Every tea I have tried has been out of this world. Always an amazing experience with minimal wait times and a cozy and clean establishment.
Great service and very helpful!
Veggie Banh Mi was pretty delicious.
Not good, just ice, lacks flavor.. too expensive for just ice
Came in for bubble tea, which were delicious. It smelled amazing in there so I’ll have to come back to try the food.
It's okay. Beverages were good, awkward atmosphere though. Might just be an off day judging from the other ratings.
This place is a hidden gem. I really miss Taiwan, and even though this is Vietnamese, they have mastered the art of bubble tea. We'll definitely come back!
Garbage!

Popped in today with my family after church.   What an amazing surprise.   Charlotte has great spots yet because it’s such a transplant city, you can easily get caught up in big box and corporate eateries.  This place is a neighborhood gem that feels extremely genuine and is indeed quickly becoming one of my favorite spots.   Had teas, tea cakes, smoothies, etc.   next week, I’ll be moving on to the beautiful looking bahn mi sandwiches and some finger foods.   If it’s as good as it looks, I’ll be back for another review.

Gotta love the soul and integrity of family owned businesses.
Summer Breeze tea with mango popping and grilled pork banh mi were very tasty. I’ll be back for sure.
The foods in there are refreshing.
Best bahn mi sandwiches & smoothies around! Reasonable prices & super friendly staff. 10/10!
I recommend the strawberry kiss
Delicious food, large variety of teas, sandwiches, and finger foods like fried tofu are also great. Prices are fair and reasonable.

I come here once a week while we're running errands and I always look forward to getting tea from them! The space is always clean and has a cozy atmosphere, and the staff are friendly. Whether it's a milk tea, a fruit tea, or a coffee, their drinks are all fantastic and there are no bad choices really. They also have some great sandwiches and desserts that I highly recommend.

really yummy low-key boba shop! I love that they added sugarcane drinks that are made in house. The Thai tea is my favorite because its brewed tea, not powder! Their milk teas are always my go to because it's not made with powder unlike some other places. As far as food goes, the banh mi is always fresh and delicious (would recommend the house special, grilled pork, or bulgogi). However, the meat patties (they have chicken or pork) are my absolute favorite! They are so crispy with flavorful meat on the inside. Highly recommend and support small family owned businesses!

First time here! We got a Wildberry tea with bubbles & Honey Milk tea with bubbles. Super good & original taste! Plus they sell Vietnamese foods & deserts which we have to come back & try. We do apologize for coming in 5 minutes before closing, but the employees were super nice. Thank you <3

Hidden gem! The on site manager is really friendly and you can tell he really cares about the quality of beverages and food served. This site has a wide variety of drinks and makes for a perfect quick stop to get refreshments. We tried the Vietnamese coffee and matcha cheesecake— both were delicious.

They also serve Vietnamese sandwiches.
Best boba tea in Charlotte- I always get the taro milk tea 1/2 sweet so good! Always smells so clean inside too. I’m told the food is awesome too but I’ve never tried it. Support small businesses!
Amazing Banh Mis and atmosphere. Great service and staff.
Very good and delicious. Definitely would come back ☺.

I have visited this place with some time to kill and I had the mango mason jar. I love the fruit in the mason jar and also the decorated fruit. This is a great drink. Definitely get it and also the guy at the front on the register was very nice to me that we go to the spot if you like Boba or tea it was very pretty inside as well which I really enjoyed. I love when a store feels very comforting and pretty.

The vanilla bean latte is my favorite thing in the world. I used to stop by occasionally for a milk tea when I was in the area (and I do vaguely remember they were good), but one day I got the vanilla bean latte on a whim and now my life is changed and that's the only thing I ever get here. I've probably gotten it about 10 times at this point and its always delicious & perfect every time. Obsessed.

Oh, and the staff is always great and the shop is cute, too. :)
This place has amazing food, atmosphere and service. The owner is very friendly, cool guy. Go here now!! I got the #10 (bulgogi)+egg rolls & left with a vanilla bean latte.🥰
Fantastic coffee, bubble tea and bahn mi! Fresh ingredients and wonderful service make this a great place.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Lemongrass Tofu Banh MI, Popcorn Chicken, Lemongrass Chicken

reviews_data.review_text: I always have great service and the food and boba are the best!
Best tea/ drinks in Charlotte, hands down. I try something new on the menu every time I come in and am never disappointed!
Delicious Lemongrass Tofu (dry) Bahnmi sandwich.
Un ambiente agradable
I love the attention and care that was given by the staff. I'll definitely be back.
I love this tea house! The staff was so friendly. My order was delicious. I wish I had more to say, but it was just 10/10 and I was in and out in 10 minutes. 🥰
I love this place! Staff is very friendly. The drinks are good and the cream brûlée is the bomb!!!!
Got the lemongrass chicken bahn mi and it was soooooo yummy.
Gongcha is legit and Share tea is nice but this is my spot! Clean, chill, quick, plus yummy food! Parking can be tight but I've always found a spot.
Loved the milk boba 💕 tea

My friends introduced me to this place, and I will say, It was an amazing experience!
The place was very lovely on the inside and I had no idea this place existed!
I would highly recommend the mango drink and a bulgogi sammich! The flavors are very strong with a touch of spice from the kimchi!
Staff were very nice, the passion fruit green tea boba and popcorn chicken is delicious!
All of their menu is good, staff is awesome. Highly recommend for singles, couples and families. Thank you for being a hidden gem.
Friendly service, great banh mi and great Viet Coffee as well
cute shop and has the best lychee black tea ever and no wait time, they never disappoint, every time im in the area i have to come

By far the best boba in NC, perfectly cooked pearls and wonderfully flavored tea, at a price less than half that of its competitors! Great fresh food, wonderful customer service, and a cute pleasant atmosphere. I don’t write reviews for places I like much, but I would feel guilty if I didn’t leave a good review.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Tofu Banh MI with Green Tea Bubble Tea

reviews_data.review_text: okay this is the best popcorn chicken ever and brown sugar boba is incredible also kinda cheap
A great spot to grab a yummy banh mi and a Thai tea!
I thought lula has the best Vietnamese coffee, til I tried this sea salt viet ice coffee!  I always love central tea house ice coffee but with this sea salt foam. Genius! Love it!

Great hole in the whole that many people don't know about they have amazing taro,mango, and pina-cola teas. I'm working my way down the list and haven't even gotten to their smoothies yet.and its all dairy free.

Wow! Just Wow! The Organic Matcha Latte with Coffee jellies is an absolute must try. My son ordered a coffee latte with coffee jellies. Love this place. We also ordered the grilled pork and the lemongrass chicken Banh Mi. Fantastic food and yummy drinks.
Really good coffee milk teas. Great food at affordable prices. Really nice owner.

I absolutely LOVE Central Tea House and I go here a lot! This was the first place where I ever tried banh mi, and it’s still the best I’ve had. Their lemongrass tofu banh mi is amazing. The veggies are always fresh and so flavorful.

Their boba tea is equally tasty, and some of my faves are: wintermelon, Thai, Central (their signature), and brown sugar milk tea.

Phu, the owner, is super nice, and I love supporting a locally-owned business!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Lemongrass Tofu, Fruit Danish, Lemon Black Tea

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Evangelia for your review, patron and support!

reviews_data.review_text: Really nice, well done place. Very clean and attentive. Great teas and coffee.

Good clean service. They make a decent vietnamese sandwich which is what makes me come back.  In comparison to other places this has to be the more delicious and better valued sandwich of the CLT area. Their boba is top notch & the plaza has some of the better stores of the city! Staff is nice and the cafe is clean. Don’t expect anything special with their food because it’s clearly not a full blown restaurant. I am a regular boba tea connoisseur and recommend this spot!
Delicious Boba, great customer service, clean shop. What's not to like?!
Coffee milk tea was great! Bahn mi was good too

Definitely don’t go here if you’re in a rush. However everything is delicious. The teas were awesome and the people are so sweet. Get the pork pastry!! So good and so yum. Just takes a little while but it’s made to order. 9/10. Would definitely go again.

Couldn’t order a veggie only banh mi sandwich.. Literally just don’t add any meat or tofu.

I offered to pay for a tofu sandwich and asked them to not add the tofu. The woman at the register said they can’t do that.

So you mean to tell me you HAVE to add meat to a sub even though the customer doesn’t want it? You can’t just leave the veggies on as is?

The chef is literally behind you just ask them to not add meat to it.

Very annoying considering we spent $20+ on drinks.

There is a very nice and calm coffee shop type of atmosphere. I ordered a Vietnamese coffee and added coffee flavored jellies which was delicious. We enjoyed the pastries and the food, too. Menu pricing was very affordable compared to the inflated prices I am used to seeing now a days. To top it all off the staff was so kind. We will be coming back often.

No matter how good the drinks/food are... its always the same 2 moody girls that just seem like they are deeply unhappy with their job and it reflects with how they interact with their customers. The older and younger guy are nice at least.
Very cute little tea shop with friendly service and delicious bubble tea. An hour away from my home and I'll be coming again.

Soooo I went yesterday for the first time. Taste wise it was solid 9/10! The boba wasn't watered down at all. The popping boba was real and natural tasting unlike most shops. But… I don’t know how I felt about the service. I ordered the butterfly pea tea with lychee popping boba + regular boba. I received it and it looked great, although, I got the wrong toppings. I let them know they were the wrong toppings, apologizing. Maybe they were just tired but they seemed very annoyed. Once they returned… my butterfly pea tea was brown? Please someone tell me why is brown.. I thought it was the base they used but it should just be butterfly pea flowers in water, not another tea. I will change my review higher once I am aware that I actually got what I ordered. Because this was my first time ordering it, I know its supposed to be blue/purple but I don’t know how it tastes so I cant tell wether they got it wrong again or not, I was too afraid to ask.
So good 😍

Excellent tea, service, atmosphere, and music!

Update: still the best place eand price in the city! My favorite is their Taro smoothie with Boba.

Such a cute little tea
shop! My son and his friend wanted to try it so we drove the 40 min for the experience (we had dinner next door) and it was WORTH it. The teas we tried were delicious. I enjoyed my Honeydew slush so much I forgot to get pictures of the kids’ teas 😅

The restroom had a lock code, which is genius to make sure it stays clean and is still accessible to patrons. It’s important to have clean bathrooms ok? Even the bathroom was cute—and super clean. Which matters and gives confidence to me in a food establishment.

Can’t wait to go back and try more combos of teas, and that Matcha Cheesecake.
Very prompt
They have so many drink choices!

First time at Tea House. Very nice place and clean inside. Very nice ppl and very respect to customers, love the bubble tea. You guys should go check it out. The smoothie are very tasty, it good for hot day. Go check it out. 👍
Best boba tea in town!

My friend took me here on one of the hottest days in Charlotte so far. They had so many different types of teas, smoothies etc. I had the Taro Boba and it was outrageous. I love that you could order less sugar too. Can’t wait to go back.
Delicious teas and kind staff!!
Quick and easy service. Drinks are light and delicious 😋
Amazing Bahn mi, definitely recommend

I  come here every time I go to pick up my pets food. The staff is helpful and friendly and they have SEVERAL teas to choose from.  I have only had one that I didn't like. You can honestly get lost in the menu. Just try a new one each time you go but I will say the Peach Black Tea is my favorite! The food is amazing as well!
Hidden gem in Charlotte. You have to try this place. Milk tea, smoothies, great finger foods, and Banh Mi's

This is one of the few places in Charlotte to get flavored shave ice, also known as "snow"! $5.25 for your choice of flavor (we got taro), plus 3 toppings. It's the perfect, light dessert!

In addition to the usual boba milk tea choices, they also have banh mi sandwiches and other Taiwanese snacks we're looking forward to trying another time!

The "Sea Salt" series drinks must be an acquired taste. We tried a wintermelon sea salt milk tea, and it was definitely more salty than sweet. Not really to our liking, but glad we tried.
First impression, the blended boba tea was awesome! Taro is always my go-to flavor. Will definitely come back and try their Banh Mi next time too.
The best boba I have had thus far. im regretful I waited this long to come here.  I have tried a lot of tea houses by now and nothing can compare to them.
If you are addicted to sweets like my wife... This is the place to get your fix.
Great atmosphere and amazing tea, I recently moved to Charlotte and started working in the same shopping center and this will be my come to when I’m at work or just want a snack and drink one day

Great experience everyone here is wonderful. Great teas should check them out. Better than where I usually get chi tea. Also my son who’s three and is very picky loves there shaved strawberry with passion jelly and strawberry popping. If you know read this is the best place ever !!!!!
Got the Thai tea boba and lemongrass tofu banh mi, they were both very good! Maybe the best boba I've ever had, the pearls were so soft and just a great texture!
Great sandwiches and milk tea selection! Clean and cozy inside too, makes for a nice date.
They had great drinks and food!
love this small business! friendly, excellent service, and the best boba in town in my opinion.
Excellent boba
I usually never posts reviews, but this place deserves it. The milk teas with boba are absolutely delicious. I’ve tried a myriad of boba spots in Charlotte, and this one is by far the best.
The only boba place I like.
Accommodating and the tea is good. Consider halving the sugar though.

I’ve been here a couple times but I haven’t gotten the chance too review it but today I have some time. First I’d like too say the place is quite small but the atmosphere just screams peaceful, there are also plants on every table so it makes it nicer. They maintain the COVID guidelines which is 6 feet apart.
I had their strawberry smoothie boba and it was very refreshing, they have music playing in the background so it lightens the mood for anyone who might be in a terrible mood.
I’ve also just found out they have board games that you can play while drinking boba so that’s something else. They have sandwiches on their menu as well but those I haven’t tried yet so I can’t review those yet but other then that I recommend this place highly too anyone who wants too bring their date here.
I loved them so much the boba WAS AWESOME my mother loved the food as well my friend also enjoyed the boba her ABSOLUTELY RECOMMEND if you like bakery’s and boba😎✌🏽💖
First time trying. Very good experience.  Like oreo milk tea
Awesome banh mi. Vanilla milk tea is amazing
small place—would highly recommend for its excellent service and quality food/drinks. definitely making this a regular hangout!
Great mangonada and delicious Banh mi!
Lowkey spot with good boba and fast service. Diverse food options as well. Would recommend!
delicious tea, especially the winter melon fruit tea. it’s very low-key but definitely don’t overlook it. one of my favourite bubble tea places in charlotte

They have a very diverse choice of teas. They give you the choice of cold or hot for almost all options. Their egg tart was delicious as well. It's a nice spot to hang out inside or outside. There are two tables inside and two outside. If you're looking to try a new tea spot, this one is worth looking at.

The owner is very friendly and their bulgolgi banh mi is an absolute favorite of mine! This is also the only place where I was able to find egg tarts (or natas) and I can’t stop coming back for them. :) Love this place

Absolutely amazing here....the mega mango with rainbow 🌈 jelly's is brilliant it has little pieces of apples 🍎 and other fruits in it as well. And menu item #2 which is a sandwich is Devine. And the cute tea cake 🎂 is 🔥
1. Its a cozy little spot.
2.staff super friendly
3. Price's are like $9 and lower!!
4.support small business
Will return ...have return ....will continue to return!!
I just moved to the area 2 weeks ago and really like this place. I’ve already visited 3 times for tea
Best tea in town!

Stopped in for lunch after a hike and had the best experience! The Thai boba tea was fantastic, with perfect soft squishy boba. The real shing star was the bulgogi bahn mi. It's ruined me for all other sandwiches. Do your self a favor and get the egg add on. I just left and already can't wait to go back!
This place is the best! I always recommend Central Tea House for their delicious food, amazing drinks and wonderful people working there.
Deserves more love!!
the people there are sooo nice great boba I really recommend coming here!😁
Poor customer service! Even when owner be cashier ! When I try to order , He was rushing me at that time!

I stumbled on this cafe by chance and I’m glad I did. Their prices are quite affordable and they have a wide range of drink selections as well as snacks and pastries. Such as a variety of tea and bánh mì. Their boba is soft and chewy which is really good. My favorite is their oolong milk tea with 50% sugar.
I really like the vibe here. Good tea and sandwiches.
The best customer service, and the drinks are so good!!
The taro smoothie is great, all the pastries are awesome, and the BULGOGI sandwich is A1! The guy at the counter was super friendly, helpful, and incredibly polite. Will absolutely be coming back.
Had the tres leaches & passion tea~ very nice service & great tea plus the tres leaches was aromatic & delicate!
Great drink selection. Fun and family friendly. Delicious tea and Báhn Mi. Owner is very friendly. It’s very close to my job so I’ve found a new spot for after work!!!
This place is AMAZING and it is only my first time there mango green tea with boba and lychee jelly is to die for. And there is also a variety of drinks to choose from.I hope I come here more often
The food is delicious. The wide variety of teas are amazing. They have more than 20 different teas.

I used to go almost EVERY DAY when I worked close to here! The staff and owners are so wholesome, welcoming, and friendly here. The service is quick and the food is not only exceptionally priced but super delicious! My go to is the number 7 with a added egg and a raspberry lemon black tea with lychee popping pearls. It is a small shop which I love cause it's so cute! They also have really yummy deserts that they make there and little board games too! This place deserves more recognition for sure! 10/10 would recommend!!!
Everything here is worth double the price, especially the bahn mi. Phu's service is way superior and genuine as well.
Food and boba is on point!
Huge menu. Friendly service. Adorable set up.
Very friendly staff, good to have a small chat with. Tea was on top level. We've been to every bubble tea place in Charlotte, I definitely recommend this place. A+👌

I ordered a oolong milk tea, and it turned out extremely milky, and with no tea flavor at all.  Explained to the manager and tried to be nice about it and ended up being treat badly in return.  Not very good customer service.
The one on the right is the milky one, and I did not drink it.  Please be the judge.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello.  I apologize regarding the Oolong Milk Tea. I was trying to explain our policy of no refund or returns.
The picture on the right is the Oolong Milk Tea and the left is a Black Milk Tea. They are two different types of Milk Tea which produce different tastes and colors. You asked for exchange of the Oolong Milk Tea for a Black Milk Tea which we don’t mind exchange but not our policy. Sorry again for the situation and confusion.

reviews_data.review_text: Very nice cozy clean dining area. Quality drinks and food. Must see!
I love this place! Amazing prices on sandwiches and so yummy. I like the lemongrass tofu and sea salt viet coffee. The coffee could be addicting it’s so good.
This might be our new favorite boba place in town! The tea is fresh and there is a huge variety of drinks to try.

Service is quick. Tons of options for snacking. They even have games for you to play with friends. Definitely a great place for a quick hangout. The taro smoothie is pretty good. 👌 the shaved ice from San Fran has made my expectations too high so i didnt really care for the shaved ice here. Definitely will return to try out now things on the menu.
Delicious milk tea! Love the mochi topping!
Best boba tea I’ve had in Charlotte so far!
Best bubble tea on this side of town!
Loved all
The boba tea is amazing! There are so many drinks to choose from!

I would highly recommend you give it a try. Really good experience with owner, food, Boba tea, price, and setting. I will definitely be returning. I hope they out grow their present location, which is a small storefront shop.

We wanted a quick bite before a game, and decided on Vietnamese. We were going to stop at a Pho place, then we saw this next door. So glad we did! We ordered taro boba teas, a traditional banh mi pork sandwich, lemongrass chicken sandwich, and a traditional pork and egg steamed bun. Everything was delicious! My only remark is to ask for the bang mi buns to be less toasted (my preference).

The owner is super sweet and staff seem to enjoy their jobs, which makes for a great experience. They also offer pastries like: Napoleans, Tres Leches, Macaroons, cake slices, and cookies. Their milk tea, smoothie, and drink selection is vast, which I look to explore later.
Best Boba I ever taste in Charlotte, I’ve been everywhere.

This place was AMAZING. My wife and I are pretty picky with our bubble tea. We normally drive like an hour for some good bubble tea until we found this place. The flavor is delicious and creamy. They have a lot of options as well. We were definitely satisfied with our experience.
Good variety of offerings both in bahn mi and tea
love that they have bahn mis!

Amazing place for Bubble Tea, food, and dessert. The staff is always friendly and willing to assist any customer with their order. It is a great place to relax and grab a bite and play games with friends. My girlfriend and I love going here!
The pudding is very good, not too sweet or too eggy. Haven’t tried all the tea yet but the Fruity ones we got were good.

Cute little place with just a few small tables. It is a tea house, not a sit down restaurant. There must be 50 different types of tea! We tried three different ones and really enjoyed them. Be warned however, they can be VERY sweet. They have different levels of sweetness. Be sure to pick the one that matches your taste buds.

Food was great too. It was the best part. We had several sandwiches that were unusual and delicious. Great, distinct flavors. Unusually good bread.
Staff is wonderful!!!! They're like my asian family outside of my family!!!! Great selection of teas!!!!
Very delicious drinks!

This has to be one of the BEST places in Charlotte get banh mi and bubble tea!  The owner is Vietnamese, extremely sweet and friendly. This place offers a hospitable atmosphere to hang out with friends and/or get good food on the go. I will definitely return for more food!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your business and review.

reviews_data.review_text: U need to get there day dreamer special fruit tea its sooo good won't regret it and there sandwiches are the bomb as well really nice staff as well
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your business and the positive review.

reviews_data.review_text:
I love everything. I love the Bahn mi. My favorite is the bulgogi- it's a Korean BBQ, it's so good and the teas and smoothies are real fruit and milk!

I eat there multiple times a week. No regrets!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for your business and the review.

reviews_data.review_text: I love the boboa tea here! Thai tea is my favorite
Very nice Banh mi and boboa tea shop, everyone was pleasant. The boboa tea is really good! There’s a wide variety and I can’t wait to try more!
Great food at very reasonable prices! A+
Disappointed. Over priced, long wait.. and no the place wasn’t even busy. Not sure why there are so many positive reviews on here. Maybe I’ll visit again and try out the food.... maybe.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Jessie. Thanks for your comment. We apologize for your negative experience. We were inexperienced than and since have learned from our mistakes. Hope you give us a second chance to gain your business and your appetite.

reviews_data.review_text: Pretty good tea joint, one of the only on the Central Blvd area. Small lounge area, but nicely decorated. Only thing I can say that I dislike is that toppings are at an added cost, whereas generally places like these toppings are generally free for one or 2, and then anymore is an extra cost.
My new favorite boba spot in Clt!! Such a convenient location, great drink selection, & everything is so fresh and greatly flavored!! Highly recommend!
Stopped in for tea today and loved it! Adorable tea/sandwich shop with a friendly staff. Great place to grab a quick bite to eat.

The place is nice.  Bright and welcoming!
Counter service with a smile (or 2).  It's in a good location as it's in the same plaza as the best Pho in Charlotte. I would save some room for an after pho smoothie or tea.  They have a lot of options so they will have what you want.  I had the original banh mi and it ranks up there with one of the best in Charlotte.  Definately stop by!
Amazing customer service! The drinks are delicious as well. They have lots of teas! You can even ask them to put it in a mason jar for you.

The shoppe is clean, the atmosphere is cozy, relaxing and the staffs are friendly. We wish we can come here everyday, bánh mì is delicious and a great way to go with bubble drink, so far we try four different bánh mì and all good. Definitely recommend.
Thank you so much and best wishes.

We had the Beach Bum tea, an Oreo shake and shared a Chicken sandwich. Everything was really good. So good that I ordered the beef sandwich and another Beach Bum tea to go. I’ll be back for sure to try different flavors!

Recommending this place for great boba tea (Sea Salt Matcha Latte is my favorite) and banh mi (Grilled Pork or Red Pork are my personal favorites) The staffs was helpful in recommending and explaining the menu. Will definitely be back.
This place is great! The variety seems endless and everything is really good. Really love their BahMi’s, especially their #7 grilled red pork and #10 bulgogi
That banh mis are delicious! They have a large variety of drinks which is impressive. My favorite drinks are the milk teas and sea salt drinks! Its a great place to visit with friends and family.

Place is amazing! The employees were so nice and very fast! I got the Central milk tea and it was super good! I can't wait to try more drinks because they have such a variety to choose from. They also have some fried foods along with Banh mi. Overall was a good experience, definitely recommend.

I was really excited for this place to open but was pretty disappointed. First of all, this is a tea house and it smells like funky seafood. It doesn’t give it a pleasant atmosphere or really give you much of an appetite for food or tea. Then I ordered a coconut milk tea, which was just okay. The tea tasted pretty great but the tapioca pearls were over cooked and mushy. For a simple order, and for a new restaurant, that doesn’t bode well. Overall, it’s not bad but I’d rather order a drink/food from Pho Hoa right next door (which I love). However, the menu is pretty expansive and offers unique drinks not easily available in Charlotte and I could have just caught a bad day. I’d give it another shot for sure. I hope things improve!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Hannah
Our apology for your negative experience. Since than, we have learned from our mistakes and made changes for a better customer experiences. Hope you will give us a second chance to gain your business. Thanks for your comment.

reviews_data.review_text: Great place for Vietnamese sandwich and milk tea. I love it!
